  @attribute='Text "Quote" More text'

 it can go both ways!!!

 going from child element to parent element example :
 //div[@id='flash-messages']//parent::div[@class='row']

moving between preceding siblings example
//div[@id='content']//preceding-sibling::div[@class='row']

//ul//li



Css Selector ( css selector doesnt work with element text)

[attribute='value'][attribute='value']

ShortCuts

id --> # --> example  #value
class --> . --> example .value

> or space moves to the next element

contains:
     * --> refers to contains
  [id*='partial-value']

Starts-with
  ^ --> refers to starts-with
  [id^='partial-value-from-beginning']

Ends-with
   $ --> refer to ends-with
  [id$ ='partial-value-from-ending']


  :first-of-type --> selects first element from a list of sibling elements
  :last-of-type --> selects last element from a list of sibling elements
  :nth-of-type(n) --> selects n th element from a list of sibling elements

  class="btn btn-primary"
  class="btn btn-primary first-button"  --> .btn.btn-primary.first-button

  .btn.btn-primary not(first-button)

  not keyword is going to look for an element that has the mentioned class value pieces
  without the indicated NOT class piece

  1st, 2nd, 3rd ,4th...nth

css selector table element
#table1 tbody tr td:nth-of-type(4)
















